 <H1>Concurrency Control</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Concurrent execution of user programs             is essential for good DBMS performance.
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Because disk accesses are frequent, and relatively slow, it is important to keep the cpu humming by working on several user programs concurrently.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Interleaving actions of different user programs can lead to inconsistency: e.g., check is cleared while account balance is being computed.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>DBMS ensures such problems don’t arise:  users can pretend they are using a single-user system.</H2>
</UL></P>
